intercept the following system call:
execve()- used to launch external programs for specififc users.  Modify the call 
so that if a bash shell is invoked for a specific normal user then make it a root shell

Test by sshing into the local system and logging in as that user and making sure you get a root shell on longin

Intercept 2 more system calls of your choice.  Use strace on different commands to find interesting system calls to intercept.  

